[method_1] I'd suggest twisting the tooth with dental floss to help it come out quicker (watch that it doesn't fall out before your vacation);
[method_2] Pinch the area with your thumb and index finger to gently pull it out, but try not to hurt yourself;
what_not_to_do = Avoid pulling out teeth with tools like pliers or screwdrivers (those aren't really designed for this purpose);
safety_tip = Since the tooth should fall out naturally in a few days, don't worry if it doesn't fall out right away; it's normal for it to be loose, it's not a sign that something is wrong with you
